The representation of the mapping class group 

The mapping class group  consists of
diffeomorphisms of the Riemann surface  which are
not isotopic to the identity. It is generated by the Dehn-twists, 
which act on an annulus  in the way indicated in Figure 
. 

7cm
dehn2.eps  
Action of a Dehn-twist on an annulus. 
Elements  will map any
graph drawn on the surface , in particular
any triangulation of , into another one. Since any
two triangulations can be connected by a sequence of elementary moves
one may represent any element  by the 
corresponding sequence of flips. This means that the 
mapping class group  is a subgroup of 
the Ptolemy groupoid .

It is extremely useful to think of
the algebraically complicated mapping class group  
as being embedded into the Ptolemy groupoid.




